 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNESBURG A highly anticipated meeting between head of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid), Robert McBride and Acting SAPS Commissioner, Kgomotso Phahlane, is taking place in Parliament on Tuesday.McBride told MPs that Phahlane should be suspended, saying the acting national commissioner of police instructed witnesses not to cooperate with an investigation.Acting Police Commissioner, Kgomotso Phahlane hit back saying the Ipid was captured and dysfunctional, vehemently denying that he was corrupt.Phahlane says himself and his wife are both employed and earn a combined R2.5-million.The two have been at loggerheads over allegations against Phahlane and claims by McBride that police are involved in a drugs syndicate at OR Tambo International Airport.READ: McBride fires salvos at Phahlane, SAPS and HawksParliament requested both heads attend a meeting where it will interrogate reports of interference in Ipid's work by SAPS.The meeting is taking place at the Old Assembly Chamber.eNCA